  "_template_instructions": {
    "to_add_a_new_market": [
      "1. Copy one of the market blocks above (e.g. 'nyc') and rename the key (e.g. 'miami')",
      "2. Update linkedin_geo_urn — find yours at linkedin.com/jobs/search then inspect the geoId param",
      "3. Replace sports_teams with teams in your market (ESPN team IDs at espn.com/[sport]/teams)",
      "4. Replace data_sources with your city/county open data APIs",
      "5. Update price_benchmarks with local comps",
      "6. In Make.com: clone S14/S15 (LinkedIn search), update geoUrn and market param to your new key",
      "7. In Make.com: clone S1/S5 (ESPN athletes), update team IDs",
      "8. In Supabase isa_leads: the 'market' column accepts any string — just use your new key"
    ],
